Did you notice those are the levels for the Note spells?  And what is the effect on the item returned from the Aqi note?  I bet it's level 50, whatever it is.<br>
<br>
What if you need to make a Note, turn it in for an item, then make a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>different</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> note to match the effect level of the item?<br>
<br>
For example, making the Bep Note requires level 44 spells, but the effect is level 39.<br>
<br>
So now what if you make the level 39 Aqi Note?  Perhaps use the A Note and the Amulet of Knowledge somehow together?<br>
<br>
A Note + Amulet?<br>
A Note + Amulet + Parchment (Storebought) + Quill?<br>
<br>
And what of the Rune-Word creations?  Perhaps those factor in here as well, now that we've found two valid combines for them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nirrudn@themagicianstower>Nirrudn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#333333>(12/5/02 11:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1115.topic&index=313>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re:</span><hr size=1> Can't edit my above post, but I just saw the effect on the Aqi Note's item is Storm Strength.  That's 53 for Rangers and 44 for Druids, but it does scale up to exactly level 50. (Probably just because it's an old world spell though)<br>
